Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with 1/2 tsp of @salt{} for the linguine.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them onto a piece of #foil with a drizzle of @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel.

When the #oven is hot, pop the parcel onto one side of a large #baking tray{} and roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the #pot. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @pine nuts{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #small bowl{} and set the pan aside.

When the tomatoes have roasted for about 10 mins, lay the @Serrano ham{2%slices} onto the other side of the #baking tray{} and cook for the remaining roasting time until crisp and golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Pop the (now empty) #frying pan{} back on high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

When hot, add the @monkfish medallions{200%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} each side, adjusting the heat as needed. Stir the garlic in with the fish for the final min.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate and cover to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The monkfish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Pop your frying pan back on medium heat (no oil) with the @crème fraîche{75%g}, @fresh pesto{50%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}. Stir together and bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir through the @peas{120%g}, cooked linguine and half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40%g}. Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything is ready, share the pesto linguine between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the roasted tomatoes (discard the juices in the foil) and top with the monkfish.

Finish by sprinkling with the toasted pine nuts and the remaining Parmigiano Reggiano, then a Serrano shard on top. Enjoy!